, and a deeply-forked tail. Both sexes are indistinguishable from each other. Behavior It is a forest bird as other drongos that can is confined to forest edges, plantations, and wooded gardens. Like most drongos, it feeds on insects from open perches. A superb mimic of the calls of other birds but always has a metallic sound. References Rasmussen, P.C., and J.C. Anderton. 2005. Birds of South Asia. The Ripley guide. Volume 2: attributes and status. Smithsonian Institution and Lynx Edicions, Washington D.C. http://www.ceylonbirdclub.org/ceylon_bird_club_search.php?id=48", "shortSummary": "The Sri Lanka drongo (Dicrurus lophorinus) or Ceylon crested drongo, is a species of bird in the family Dicruridae. It is endemic to Sri La…", "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/31/Dicrurus_lophorinus_63119961.jpg/960px-Dicrurus_lophorinus_63119961.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-dicrurus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-dicrurus-lophorinus", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-dicrurus", "species": "taxonomy-species-dicrurus-lophorinus"}, "expandable": true, "x": 985.43, "y": 232.68, "z": -241.0}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-dicrurus", "name": "Dicrurus", "latinName": "Dicrurus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Dicrurus（Dicrurus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联28种鸟类，如古铜色卷尾、小盘尾、鸦嘴卷尾等28种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 28, "x": 597.53, "y": 354.92, "z": -4.97}], "links": [{"key": "bird-sri-lanka-drongo-36895f75__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-dicrurus-lophorinus", "source": "bird-sri-lanka-drongo-36895f75", "target": "taxonomy-species-dicrurus-lophorinus", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-dicrurus-lophorinus__belongs_to_gen